value.value: At least one tumor is greater than 3 mm in largest dimension or located closer than 1.5 mm to the optic nerve or fovea.  No retinal detachment or subretinal fluid beyond 5 mm from the base of the tumor. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

At least one tumor is greater than 3 mm in largest dimension or located closer than 1.5 mm to the optic nerve or fovea, with retinal detachment or subretinal fluid beyond 5 mm from the base of the tumor.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
Tumors no more than 2/3 the volume of the eye with vitreous or subretinal seeding.  Can have retinal detachment.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
Focal vitreous and/or subretinal seeding of fine aggregates of tumor cells is present, but no large clumps or "snowballs" of tumor cells. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ann Arbor Stage I Primary Mediastinal Large B-Cell Lymphoma

value.value: Ann Arbor Classification: Stage I: Involvement of a single lymph node region (I); or localized involvement of a single extralymphatic organ or site in the absence of any lymph node involvement (IE).
Massive vitreous and/or subretinal seeding is present, defined as diffuse clumps or "snowballs" of tumor cells. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
Severe intraocular disease. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
Tumor fills more than 2/3 of the eye. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

One or more complications are present, which may include tumor-associated neovascular or angle closure glaucoma, tumor extension into the anterior segment, hyphema, vitreous hemorrhage, or orbital cellulitis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
Extraocular disease detected by imaging studies. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
Invasion of the optic nerve. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
Invasion into the orbit. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
Intracranial extension not past chiasm. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
Intracranial extension past chiasm. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Retinoblastoma Clinical Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of retinoblastoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Ann Arbor Stage II Primary Mediastinal Large B-Cell Lymphoma

value.value: Ann Arbor Classification: Stage II: Involvement of two or more lymph node regions on the same side of the diaphragm (II); or localized involvement of a single extralymphatic organ or site in association with regional lymph node involvement with or without involvement of other lymph node regions on the same side of the diaphragm (IIE).
Retinoblastoma in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
Retinoblastoma with no regional lymph node involvement. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
Retinoblastoma with regional lymph node involvement (preauricular, cervical, submandibular). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
Retinoblastoma with distal lymph node involvement. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

A mannose-binding lectin originally isolated from jack-bean, Canavalia ensiformis. Concanavalin A is a potent lymphocyte mitogen and a stimulator of matrix metalloproteinases, thereby exhibiting immunostimulatory effects. It is used in the characterization and purification of glycoproteins.

label.value: Retinoblastoma Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of retinoblastoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.
Retinoblastoma with no metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
Retinoblastoma with systemic metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
Single lesion to sites other than CNS. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
Multiple lesions to sites other than CNS. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ann Arbor Stage III Primary Mediastinal Large B-Cell Lymphoma

value.value: Ann Arbor Classification: Stage III: Involvement of lymph node regions on both sides of the diaphragm (III), which also may be accompanied by extralymphatic extension in association with adjacent lymph node involvement (IIIE) or by involvement of the spleen (IIIS) or both (IIIE,S).
Prechiasmatic CNS lesion(s). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
Postchiasmatic CNS lesion(s). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
Leptomeningeal and/or CSF involvement. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Lacrimal Gland TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of carcinoma of the lacrimal gland, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  No stage grouping is presently recommended for carcinoma of the lacrimal gland.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Lacrimal Gland Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of carcinoma of the lacrimal gland, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Complete resection of the mass is indicated.  The specimen should be thoroughly sampled for evaluation of histologic type and grade of tumor, size, possible presence of a preexisting pleomorphic adenoma, and surgical margins (including the periosteum).  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Lacrimal Gland Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of carcinoma of the lacrimal gland, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Carcinoma of the Lacrimal Gland pTX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the lacrimal gland in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Lacrimal Gland pT0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the lacrimal gland with no evidence of a primary tumor. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

A group of proteins isolated from the roots of pokeweed, Phytolacca americana, with hemagglutinating and mitogenic properties. Pokeweed mitogen is particularly mitogenic for lymphocytes and also agglutinates erythrocytes.

label.value: Ann Arbor Stage IV Primary Mediastinal Large B-Cell Lymphoma

value.value: Ann Arbor Classification: Stage IV: Diffuse or disseminated involvement of one or more extralymphatic organs, with or without associated lymph node involvement; or isolated extralymphatic organ involvement in the absence of adjacent regional lymph node involvement, but in conjunction with disease in distant site(s); or any involvement of the liver or bone marrow, lungs (other than by direct extension from another site), or cerebrospinal fluid.

label.value: Carcinoma of the Lacrimal Gland pT1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the lacrimal gland with tumor measuring 2 cm or less in greatest dimension with or without extraglandular extension into the orbital soft tissue. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

A class of lectins, found in beans, with hemagglutination properties. Phytohemagglutinin binds to complex oligosaccharides containing galactose, N-acetylglucosamine and mannose, causing agglutination of most mammalian red blood cell types. It induces mitosis and affects cell membrane permeability, thereby facilitating protein transport.

label.value: Carcinoma of the Lacrimal Gland pT2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the lacrimal gland with tumor measuring more than 2 cm but not more than 4 cm in greatest dimension.  Note: As the maximum size of the lacrimal gland is 2 cm, T2 and greater tumors will usually extend into the orbital soft tissue.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Lacrimal Gland pT3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the lacrimal gland with tumor measuring more than 4 cm in greatest dimension.  Note: As the maximum size of the lacrimal gland is 2 cm, T2 and greater tumors will usually extend into the orbital soft tissue.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Lacrimal Gland pT4 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the lacrimal gland with tumor invading periosteum or orbital bone or adjacent structures.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Lacrimal Gland pT4a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the lacrimal gland with tumor invading periosteum.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Lacrimal Gland pT4b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the lacrimal gland with tumor invading orbital bone.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Lacrimal Gland pT4c TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the lacrimal gland with tumor invading adjacent structures (brain, sinus, pterygoid fossa, temporal fossa).  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Lacrimal Gland Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of carcinoma of the lacrimal gland, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Carcinoma of the Lacrimal Gland pNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the lacrimal gland in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

The sodium salt of levothyroxine, a synthetic levoisomer of thyroxine (T4) that is similar to the endogenous hormone produced by the thyroid gland. In peripheral tissues, levothyroxine is deiodinated by 5'-deiodinase to form triiodothyronine (T3). T3 enters the cell and binds to nuclear thyroid hormone receptors; the activated hormone-receptor complex in turn triggers gene expression and produces proteins required in the regulation of cellular respiration; thermogenesis; cellular growth and differentiation; and the metabolism of proteins, carbohydrates and lipids. T3 also exhibits cardiostimulatory effects.
An embryonal carcinoma that develops as a primary tumor in an anatomic site other than the testis or ovary.

label.value: Carcinoma of the Lacrimal Gland pN0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the lacrimal gland with no regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
